[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Redesigning test structure**\n\nI’m considering if the instrumentation output should come from both tasks and whether it’s better to have one file instead of two. Maybe redesigning into a single class, like `SnappyLoaderTest`, with two test methods controlled by a system property would work. The standard `test` task could be configured for `snappy.test.mode=system`, while a custom task could handle `bundledSnappyTest`. I wonder if I should use `Assumptions` in the test methods to skip any prohibited tests.\n\n**Considering coding practices**\n\nI'm thinking about whether it's okay to revert a continuation marker in coding tasks. It seems like it might be used by forge automation, but I realize that the final pull request shouldn't include it. So, I’d probably go with using `git checkout` to handle that. It's one of those little details that can make a big difference! I want to make sure I approach it correctly to avoid issues later on.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0b44f9dc1e8c1183016a3dab15739081908c0091a5ef1fb0fa\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqPasorIuaC1Pqz8xmlEdhSknz-mbNup2YUx9Z0On6pbNsmq2ZmJ20YtfHilo2AXEpGyoF9j760d3aWZrBhDw7KlT5qFPyt2WpN1gnoxT0FJ_tfBpndaEeMKTRcSYp0IdbYWRYWGfx5Kx4T-17B3BbZxByIg5j2Qgl-VOugFXAYcKGon8Li_M54qTcYzrk2sPqjiIdeoILdDQxoUokP3urMTaccz1ieXml1Xwts6pYYxh2iDwS-xaGyr9dYIvQ25lnyb_G-pwZjx6nifZgbtK4q5twNK9K8zVLHL-yDgbOF1k6nA5HvHRl5fugYPsllezkxiQqdY98aZr52ShjgStYfFsAygX71yg-Tm2oYMQvDy7CGNWph_QaMWFGl8yXL2qQqsv_WDsx0b8eIiTgxXRvTfp3ac6Fg2O8ZqQPXA3CRiuRSreAsVN7k8bpNqjHv5f9T8HvBmUfsdDOM3Bpzoc8HoYA-tUb3YkCiJMDyYvfXNxaWcw7znceQAEsYZyhJCNSKuI-2910vK3XU_rlDcducbK_QeqBDeVFhSj6KrXLJZNq6Scv6q4hZP6QWWPREbkx9K8dJunYcs3SjFD3ElYQKkWe1GdDjY3XHPmeOX94j0vS5qjczLvRNtD9E3HfsJrNKoxA_dwTY65hFu856fBrjtZr2Qc-O3T0H4sfPvsI7X4xmUXXtdqKe8j3UPtlRjEAaG2J6-UZB_pNjwzox1W2izv_-r7AsmoE9pHilScSjHEzfGnlQUjL72UFcOedWzWiB2R5etBvr-